Privacy Policy for NexCare
Last Updated: October 30, 2025
At NexCare, your privacy and trust are very important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information when you use our mobile application and related services.
By using NexCare, you agree to the terms described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
   To provide you with the best healthcare experience, we may collect the following information:
   Personal Information
   First Name and Last Name
   Email Address
   Phone Number
   Emergency Contact and Phone Number
   Tax Registration Number (TRN) (optional or where legally required)
   Date of Birth
   Gender
   Address
   Medical Information
   Allergies
   Current Medications
   Medical Conditions or Illnesses
   Medical History Notes
   Usage and Technical Data
   Device Information (such as model, operating system, and app version)
   Language Preference (for multilingual support)
   Log and Usage Data (for performance and analytics)
   Payment Information
   When you make payments through the app, we collect necessary details to process transactions securely via trusted third-party payment providers.
   We do not store your full payment card information on our servers.
2. How We Use Your Information
   Your data is used to:
   Create and manage your user account
   Enable appointment booking and communication with doctors
   Provide AI-powered symptom analysis (advisory only ‚Äî not a substitute for professional diagnosis)
   Generate digital prescriptions and billing receipts
   Manage doctor availability and appointments
   Send important notifications about appointments, updates, and reminders
   Facilitate secure payments and issue receipts
   Personalize your experience across different languages
   Improve app functionality, quality, and support
3. AI Symptom Analysis
   NexCare uses AI technology to assist users in identifying possible symptoms or conditions.
   However, this feature is not a medical diagnosis tool.
   We strongly recommend consulting our licensed healthcare professionals for accurate diagnosis and treatment.
4. Data Security
   We take your privacy and data protection seriously.
   All personal and medical data is encrypted both in transit and at rest.
   Access to your data is restricted to authorized personnel and healthcare providers involved in your care.
   We use secure authentication, firewalls, and monitoring tools to prevent unauthorized access.
   We do not sell or share your personal data with unauthorized third parties.
5. Data Sharing
   Your information may be shared only when necessary:
   With healthcare providers to facilitate appointments, prescriptions, and treatment.
   With payment processors for billing and payment processing.
   With law enforcement or authorities when required by law.
   With trusted partners (such as AI service providers) under strict confidentiality agreements to improve app features.
6. Data Retention
   We retain your information only as long as needed to:
   Provide our healthcare and administrative services
   Comply with legal and regulatory requirements
   Maintain accurate medical and billing records
   You may request data deletion at any time (see Section 9 below).
7. Multilingual Support
   As a multilingual platform, we may use your selected language preference to:
   Display app content in your preferred language
   Deliver notifications and emails in the appropriate language
   Ensure consistency across devices and sessions
8. Notifications
   We send notifications for:
   Appointment reminders
   Payment confirmations
   New messages or updates from your doctor
   Health or service alerts
   You can manage or disable notifications at any time through your device settings.
9. Your Rights
   Depending on your location, you may have the right to:
   Access your personal information
   Correct or update inaccuracies
   Request deletion of your data
   Withdraw consent to data processing
   Change your language or notification preferences
   To exercise these rights, please contact us at:
